{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Home
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
	<div class="container-fluid">
		<h1>Assignment Overview</h1><br/>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-12">
				<div class="card">
					<div class="card-body">
						<h5 class="card-title">GUIDELINES</h5>
						<p class="card-text">As part of this technical interview, we would like you to demonstrate your skills with
																																																	Symfony version 7 by creating a web application that manages a list of products. Your task is
																																																	to build a CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) application with the following
																																																	functionalities:.</p>
						<ol>
							<li>Create a Product Table: Set up a database table for products with the following
																																								fields:</li>
							<ul>
								<li>ID (auto-incrementing)</li>
								<li>Name (string)</li>
								<li>Description (text)</li>
								<li>Price (decimal)</li>
								<li>Stock Quantity (integer)</li>
								<li>Created Datetime (datetime)</li>


							</ul>
						</li>
						<li>Display Products: Create a page that displays a list of products from the database in a
																												table format. Datetime column should be shown in Singapore timezone.</li>
						<li>
							Sorting: Implement sorting functionality for the table columns (Name, Price, Stock
																												Quantity. Created Datetime).</li>
						<li>Searching: Add filtering options such as filtering by price range, stock quantity, or
																												the date the product was added.</li>
						<li>
							Pagination: Implement pagination for the product list to handle large datasets.</li>
						<li>Import/Export: Provide functionality to import product data from a CSV file and
																												export the current list of products to a CSV file.</li>
						<li>
							Add/Edit/Delete: Implement functionality to add new products, edit existing
																												products, and delete products from the list.</li>
						<li>Error Handling: Enhance error handling to display user-friendly error messages and
																												log errors for debugging purposes.</li>
						<li>Performance Optimization: Optimize database queries and application performance,
																												especially for large datasets.</li>
						<li>Responsive Design: Ensure the application is mobile-friendly and responsive across
																												different screen sizes.</li>
						<li>Data Validation: Implement thorough server-side validation for all product fields to
																												ensure data integrity.</li>
					</ol>

					<p>Please use the Symfony framework to accomplish this task and ensure the following:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>
							Use Symfony 7 and adhere to best practices for project structure and coding standards.</li>
						<li>
							Utilize Doctrine ORM for database interactions.</li>
						<li>
							Create forms for adding and editing products using Symfony Form components.</li>
						<li>
							Implement necessary validation for the product fields.</li>
						<li>
							Use Twig templates for rendering views.</li>
						<li>
							Ensure the application is secure and handles errors gracefully.</li>
					</ul>

				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>{% endblock %}
